<HEADLINE>
FT  11 FEB 93 / UK Company News: Elbief deficit up to Pounds 244,000
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Shares of Elbief yesterday fell 5p to 21p as the Birmingham-based
manufacturer of photograph frames, clocks and mirrors accompanied news of an
increased interim deficit with a gloomy trading statement.
Losses before tax for the six months to October 31 increased to Pounds
244,000 (Pounds 57,000). Mr Harry Prais, chairman, said: 'Overheads were
pruned severely and employee numbers were drastically reduced, but this was
negated by lower sales.' Turnover declined 17 per cent to Pounds 1.9m.
Mr Prais said he saw little sign of an end to recession and did not
anticipate a return to profits in the current year.
Losses per share were 0.2p (0.04p).
</TEXT>
