investment, the amount of which is undisclosed, will help Basil Read develop
in South Africa and adjacent countries. Thomson-CSF, the defence electronics
arm of the French state-owned Thomson electronics group, has revealed a 2.4
per cent fall in sales last year. Turnover declined to FFr34.44bn in 1992,
from FFr35.2bn a year earlier.
