<HEADLINE>
FT  10 FEB 93 / World Commodities Prices: Market Report
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Robusta COFFEE prices closed down heavily at the London Future's and Options
Exchange in the wake of Monday night's late 5 cent fall in the New York
arabica market. London continued to be less volatile than New York, partly
because of lower fund participation. New York prices fell further in early
trading on renewed technical selling, but later were recovering some of the
losses. London dealers said the market remained very edgy. Technical factors
were still driving prices, with fundamental influences pushed firmly into
the background. On the LME ALUMINIUM and NICKEL prices, which touched
respective five and four-week highs, gave up some of the gains by the close
as the higher levels attracted profit-taking. Dealers said the strength of
both metals appeared to be technically motivated, with little news or
physical activity to justify advances. On Nymex PALLADIUM futures were
hovering near life-of-contract highs at midday as widespread worries over
near-term supplies remained the dominant factor.
Compiled from Reuters
